Xinhua news agency , Moscow , april 2 , news from Tbilisi : representatives of the united nations special representative , georgia , Abkhazia , and the cis peacekeeping force signed a protocol on georgia 's withdrawal from the Kodori mountain valley in Tbilisi on the 2nd .
according to a report by ITAR - Tass news agency , the protocol stipulates that Georgian troops should withdraw from the Kodori gorge by april 10 , while peacekeeping troops and un observers should resume patrolling the area , and all sides should ensure the safety of the residents of the area .
Berdin , special representative of the un secretary general in georgia , said that the protocol is a good signal that georgia and Abkhazia are willing to settle the conflict on the basis of mutual compromise .
the document should pave the way for further dialogue , he said .
in 1992 , the Abkhaz local authorities in georgia clashed with the Georgian government because of their demand for independence .
in october last year , there was another clash between the two sides in the Kodori gorge , to which georgia immediately sent troops .
