earlier this year , Karzai asked the un security council to expand the peacekeeping force and deploy peacekeeping troops outside the capital Kabul .
he said : this is tantamount to sending a signal that the international community has undertaken obligations to a country ravaged by 23 years of war .
Turkey has agreed in principle to take over the command of the Afghan peacekeeping force from the British .
however , fearing for the security situation outside Kabul , Turkey was not in favour of expanding the area of operation of the peacekeeping force .
the United States has expressed its support for this Turkish position .
Karzai said on the 5 th that turkey 's fear that its troops would be involved in renewed unrest outside afghanistan was superfluous .
however , he added , the afghan government will accept any decision made by countries participating in the peacekeeping force .
another sandstorm hits north china and other places
Xinhua news agency , beijing , april 6 ( reporter dong jun ) - the central meteorological station issued a sandstorm forecast at 6 : 00 pm today , saying that under the influence of strong cold air , there will be sandstorm weather in the eastern part of the northwest region , most of north china , and the central and southern part of the northeast plain from tonight to tomorrow .
the forecast says that there will be sandstorms in parts of inner mongolia 's central and southeastern eastern regions , northern Shaanxi , Shanxi , and Hebei provinces , and western Liaoning and Jilin provinces . there will be strong sandstorms in some areas , floating dust or sand uplifting in some areas of the Huanghuai river . most of these areas will be accompanied by strong winds of force 5 to 7 , and the temperature will drop by 6 to 12 degrees celsius , and the temperature in some areas will decrease by more than 14 degrees celsius .
it was sunny in beijing this morning , but a strong wind began to blow in the afternoon , driving people from outdoor activities back home one after another .
although the central meteorological station issued a forecast of gale weather in north china and other places yesterday evening , the fresh and pleasant weather has attracted many residents to take advantage of it early in the morning because of a spring rain .
today , Hohhot , the capital of inner mongolia autonomous region , also encountered a strong wind to cool down the weather .
although the north wind howled , the sky was still very clear .
experts said that spring rain fell all over inner mongolia and 33 millimeters of rain fell in the urban area of Hohhot yesterday , which not only greatly eased the drought , but also effectively curbed the invasion of dust storms .
China 's telecommunications market will exceed 1 trillion yuan by 2005
Xinhua news agency , Shanghai , april 6 ( reporter feng yizhen ) - an official of the ministry of information industry who is attending a sino - russian high - level seminar on information and telecommunications here disclosed that by 2005 , the total size of china 's telecommunications market will reach 105 billion yuan , a 2.5 - fold increase over 2000 .
according to the forecast , during the period from 2001 to 2005 , the number of telephone households in china will grow at an average annual rate of 26% , with 24% in the central and eastern regions , 26% in the central region , and 30% in the western region .
by 2005 , the number of telephone subscribers nationwide will reach 500 million , with a popularization rate of about 40% .
China 's mobile phone user base will expand to ordinary consumers and from simple messaging services to data exchange , medium - and high - speed multimedia , and high - speed interactive multimedia services .
the internet service will continue to be the fastest growing service in china 's telecommunications industry , with demand content extending from narrowband to broadband service , classified spot broadcasting service developing to high - speed interactive service , and users expanding from large and medium - sized cities to central cities and towns .
the number of data and multimedia internet users in china will grow at an average annual rate of more than 70% during the " three represents " period .
by 2005 , the number of internet users nationwide will reach 200 million .
