computer crime cost the united states billions of dollars last year
Xinhua news agency , washington , april 7 , the " 2001 computer crime and security investigation " report released by the united states on the 7th shows that the increasingly rampant computer crime caused us companies and government departments to suffer billions of us dollars in losses last year , a sharp increase over 2000 .
examples abound of computer systems in various parts of the united states being attacked by computer viruses , denial of service , and various security loopholes .
according to 538 computer security experts from enterprises , government departments , and universities , us companies and other organizations pay a high price every year for computer crimes .
although the exact amount of losses has not yet been determined , 35% of the departments surveyed admitted that they had suffered losses totaling more than 3.778 billion us dollars , up sharply from nearly 2.656 billion us dollars in 2000 .
the report , jointly compiled by the us computer security association and the federal bureau of investigation , does not provide an assessment of the losses suffered by individual users across the country .
Berber identified as official language of Algeria
Xinhua news agency , Algiers , april 8 ( reporter Xu Donghua ) - at a joint session of the two chambers of the Algerian parliament held here on the 8th , Algerian president Bouteflika submitted a draft amendment to the constitution , confirming Berber as one of the official languages recognized by the constitution .
in a speech at the meeting , Albanian prime minister ben Zavelis pointed out : the passage of the draft resolution means that the cultural diversity of argentina has been determined by law , and this will be conducive to strengthening the unity of the Albanian nation .
Berbers are indigenous inhabitants of north africa , and the number of Berbers currently living in Algeria accounts for about one - sixth of the country 's total population .
after independence , arabia 's constitution stipulated that arabic was the only official language , but the Berbers opposed it .
in april last year , serious disturbances occurred in the Kabili region of eastern argentina , where Berbers are concentrated .
more than 60 people were killed and more than 2,000 injured in the three - month - long riots .
the local people demanded that Berber be confirmed as the official language in the constitution .
in a televised speech to the nation on 12 march this year , president Bouteflika promised to meet Berbers ' demands by amending the constitution .
