East Timor presidential campaign ends
Xinhua news agency , Jakarta , april 12 , media here reported that the three - week presidential election in east Timor officially ended on the 12 th .
voters will elect on may 14 the first president of the country , which will formally become independent on may 20 .
the candidates for the presidential election are Shanana Tsangu Gusmao and Xavier Tsendo Amaral .
Gusmao is the leader of the east Timor independence movement , and do Amaral was president of the democratic republic of east Timor , which was proclaimed in november 1975 but only existed for a short time .
the two candidates held an open debate in Dili on the 11 th and answered various questions raised by voters .
Gusmao said that after his election , he would first focus on solving the country 's economic problems , and doamalar said he would ensure democracy in the country .
public opinion generally believes that Gusmao has a good chance of winning because he is regarded as the hero of east Timor 's independence .
under the auspices of the united nations , east Timor held a national referendum on 30 august 1999 , and the overwhelming majority of voters chose independence .
East Timor formally elected a constitutional assembly on august 30 last year and adopted the country 's first constitution in march this year .
the new constitution will take effect on may 20 when east Timor officially becomes independent , and the constitution - making assembly will soon become the first national assembly .
