Xinhua news agency report of april 14th from Caracas ( by staff reporter jia anping ) - Venezuelan president Hugo da Chavez , who was detained by coup soldiers two days ago , returned to the presidential palace on the 14th and was sworn in again as president of the Bolivarian republic of Venezuela amid cheers from supporters .
in his televised speech to the nation , Chavez thanked the Venezuelan people for their trust and support , thanked the organization of american states , the rio group , the group of 77 , and other international organizations for their actions in safeguarding democracy and condemning the coup d ' etat , and called on all circles in Venezuela to take conciliatory actions .
Chavez stressed that Venezuela needs peace , stability , and reason . to this end , all parties should make joint efforts to stop the conflict .
he said : through this incident , we have learned a lot . we will strive to correct past mistakes and mistakes and jointly build our country .
a coup d ' etat took place in Venezuela on november 11 , in which more than 10 senior military officers declared that they would not support the Chavez government and detained Chavez .
Carmona , former president of the Venezuelan federation of entrepreneurs , became interim president of the transitional government on Tuesday .
on the same day , supporters of Chavez staged a peaceful demonstration in the capital , demanding that Chavez return to power .
on the afternoon of the 13th , a group of soldiers who personally inspected Weiss quietly returned to the presidential palace to protect vice president Cabello , who was sworn in as interim president that evening . Carmona announced his resignation .
the pro-Chavez forces then issued an ultimatum to the coup fighters to release Chavez and occupy the important strategic stronghold of Tiuna barracks .
in the early hours of the 14 th , Chavez returned to the presidential palace by helicopter from the small caribbean island where he was detained .
