Xinhua news agency , new york , april 15 , investors are still worried about the profit prospects of listed companies because of the poor performance of Citigroup and mainland airlines . the new york stock market generally fell on the 15th , with the Dow - Jones index falling to its lowest level in eight weeks .
the Dow Jones industrial average closed down 97.15 points at 10,093.67 , the lowest level since february 22 , the technology heavy NASDAQ composite index fell 2.41 points to 1,753.78 and the s & p 500 index fell 8.46 points to 1,102.55 .
in addition , the new york stock exchange composite index and the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies also fell , with the exception of the american stock exchange index , which rose slightly .
the new york stock exchange fell to 1.12 billion shares , down from 1.26 billion in the previous session .
on the same day , Citigroup announced that due to its losses in argentina , the bank 's profit in the first quarter did not meet the expected target , and mainland airlines also announced a loss in the first quarter of this year .
the news has caused investors to be worried about the results of listed companies to be announced this week , so they have maintained a wait - and - see attitude .
the wall street stock market closed lower after a small fluctuation , and the daily turnover was also at a low level .
Blue chip stocks such as Citigroup , Continental Airlines , and General Electric , as well as Microsoft , Intel , Cisco , Oracle , Dell , and Sun Microelectronics all fell .
