Xinhua news agency , Kabul , april 16 ( reporter SHANG xuqian ) - un high commissioner for refugees luebers , who is visiting afghanistan , met with president Karzai of the afghan interim government on the evening of the 15th . the two sides held talks on the return and reintegration of afghan refugees .
the united nations refugee agency ( unhcr ) today stressed the importance of the reintegration of refugees to the stability of afghanistan .
he stressed that the security of refugees returning home must be guaranteed , and security in rural areas is very important to avoid excessive refugee flows to cities .
Karzai expressed his appreciation for UNHCR 's long - term work in afghanistan .
he said that the reintegration of refugees is one of the priorities of the interim government .
he stressed that the return of internally displaced persons to their places of origin is an urgent issue to be resolved .
he said that at present , the situation in most parts of afghanistan is stable and there is sufficient rain to enable these people to resume farming and become self - sufficient in food once they return to their places of origin .
more than 240,000 Afghans have returned home from Pakistan , 5,000 from iran and 4,000 from tajikistan since the unhcr and the afghan interim government officially began helping refugees return home on march 1 , unhcr spokesman Hassan said .
of these , 40 per cent went to the cities .
