Chinese fm spokesman comments on report adopted by european parliament
Xinhua news agency , beijing , april 19 , chinese foreign ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue today commented on a report adopted by the european parliament .
a reporter asked : on 11 april , the plenary session of the european parliament examined and adopted the report of the european parliament on the european commission 's china strategy document .
what is china 's comment on this ?
Zhang Qiyue replied : the chinese side has noticed that the european parliament recently adopted this report .
the report holds that there are extensive common interests between china and the eu , and advocates developing the sino - eu partnership , strengthening bilateral contacts , exchanges , and dialogues , and expanding bilateral cooperation in the economic , trade , scientific , technological , educational , and cultural fields .
we welcome these positive ideas .
however , the report makes many erroneous conclusions on the human rights situation in china and on the Taiwan and Tibet issues that do not conform to objective facts , and seriously interferes in china 's internal affairs . this is unacceptable to the chinese side .
it is hoped that the european parliament will earnestly abide by the one - china principle and do more things conducive to the development of bilateral relations so as not to have a negative impact on sino - eu relations .
