Xinhua news agency report of april 20th from jerusalem ( by staff reporter Zhong cuihua and ming dajun ) - Israeli government officials said on the 20th that Israel would cooperate with the commission sent by the united nations to investigate the facts in the Jenin palestinian refugee camp in the west bank .
Israeli radio quoted Israeli government officials as saying that Israel would show the un delegation videotapes documenting Israeli military operations in the Jenin refugee camp and allow members of the delegation to interview soldiers and commanders involved in military operations in the hope that the delegation would maintain objectivity and impartiality in the investigation process .
the united nations security council today unanimously adopted a resolution by the united states welcoming the investigation of the Jenin refugee camp by the un investigation team .
a few hours before the vote , Israeli foreign minister Shimon Peres telephoned un secretary general Kofi Annan to say that Israel would welcome the un representative to clarify the truth about the Jenin refugee camp .
Annan also had a telephone conversation with Israeli defense minister Benn Eliezer on the same day . Benn Eliezer also agreed to the un delegation 's investigation .
according to reports , ben Eliezer and Peres both claimed that there was a fierce exchange of fire between Israeli troops and palestinian militants during the military operation in Jenin refugee camp , killing 23 Israeli troops and 50 palestinian militants , the majority of whom were palestinian militants .
recently , there has been an upsurge in calls from the international community for an investigation into the Jenin refugee camp conflict , the most intense in the recent Israeli - palestinian conflict .
the palestinian side accused the Israeli army of massacring Palestinians there , causing hundreds of deaths , but Israel flatly denied this .
