Xinhua news agency , beijing , april 21 , chinese foreign ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue pointed out here today that the chinese side resolutely opposes Japanese leaders visiting the Yasukuni shrine where the memorial tablets of class - a war criminals are enshrined in any form and at any time .
the chinese side expressed strong dissatisfaction with this move by the Japanese leaders .
commenting on Japanese prime minister Junichiro Koizumi 's visit to the Yasukuni shrine this morning , Zhang Qiyue said : what japan has done will only damage japan 's own image and make it more difficult for japan to win the trust of the peoples of Asian countries on historical issues .
this is Junichiro Koizumi 's second visit to Yasukuni shrine since he took office .
the Yasukuni shrine is a place where Japanese soldiers who died in various wars ( mostly wars of aggression ) since the Meiji restoration are sacrificed . Hideki Tojo and other class - a war criminals from world war ii are also sacrificed here .
France holds first round of voting in presidential election
Xinhua news agency , Paris , april 21 ( reporter Liang guihe ) - the first round of voting for the french presidential election began at 8am on the 21 st in 64,000 polling stations across france .
forty million voters nationwide will vote for the seventh president of the fifth republic of france among 16 candidates .
the results of the vote were announced the same night .
voter turnout was 21.41 percent at noon on the 21 st , down from 22.52 percent in the first round of voting in the 1995 presidential election , the interior ministry said in a communique .
according to media forecasts here , this year 's turnout may set a record low in history .
the french constitution stipulates that if no candidate obtains more than 51 percent of the votes in the first round of voting , the two candidates with the highest votes will enter the second round of voting on 5 may .
last friday 's final poll results showed that incumbent president Chirac and incumbent prime minister Jospin are likely to win the first round with very close votes .
since the number of candidates in this presidential election is 16 , the highest in french history , the number of voters voting in the first round may be very scattered .
France 's far - right national front presidential candidate le pen is likely to come in third in the first round , and may even be out of the running in the top two .
