one quarter voted against or abstained from voting on the work report
NPC deputies are still not satisfied with the results of judicial system reform
more than a quarter of the deputies to the chinese national people 's congress ( NPC ) voted against or abstained from voting on the work report of the supreme people 's court and the supreme people 's procuratorate yesterday , indicating that they are still not satisfied with the reform achievements of the judicial system and the progress made in the building of the rule of law .
however , 2,742 of the 2,813 deputies who attended the closing session of the fifth session of the ninth national people 's congress at the great hall of the people voted in favor of premier zhu Zhanji 's government work report , with the approval rate still reaching 97.5% , similar to that of last year .
all sides expect that zhu zhanji , who has publicly indicated that he will retire , will withdraw from the standing committee of the political bureau at the highest decision - making level at the 16 th CPC national congress to be held this autumn .
however , the result of the vote shows that zhu hongji was not snuffed out by NPC deputies because he was about to lose power .
the 10 1 / 2 - day conference also approved the 2002 budget with a deficit of 309.8 billion yuan ( 68.8 billion Singapore dollars ) with 80.5 percent of the vote yesterday .
Li Peng , chairman of the national people 's congress [ NPC ] standing committee , made a report on the work of the NPC standing committee , which encountered slightly more opposition votes and abstained from voting than last year .
the NPC standing committee 's report received 2,587 votes in favor , 112 against , and 114 abstentions yesterday .
last year &apos;s report received 2,582 votes in favour , 85 against and 122 abstentions .
although the reaction of NPC deputies yesterday was slightly better than that of last year , as many as 28 percent and 27 percent of NPC deputies respectively voted against or abstained from voting on the work reports of the supreme people 's court and the supreme people 's procuratorate .
Xiao yang , president of the supreme people 's court , received 2,026 votes in favor , 528 against , and 259 abstentions in his work report yesterday .
his report received 1,953 votes in favour , 530 against and 306 abstentions last year .
Han zhubin , procurator general of the supreme people 's procuratorate , received 2,044 votes in favour , 516 against , and 253 abstentions in his report yesterday .
his report received 1873 votes in favour , 584 against and 332 abstentions last year .
since this year is the last session of the current NPC and the NPC will be replaced next year , the closing session yesterday also voted to adopt the " decision on the number of deputies to the 10 th NPC and the question of election , " stipulating that the 10 th NPC should be elected before the end of january next year .
China accelerates change of local party and government leaders
( Hong kong ) sources from the beijing municipal people 's congress [ NPC ] and the chinese people 's political consultative conference [ CPPCC ] disclosed to ming PAO that after the NPC and CPPCC sessions are over , the change of local party and government leaders in china will be accelerated .
the central authorities have demanded that all localities complete the work of reshuffling by the end of june this year . 17 provinces , municipalities directly under the central government , and autonomous regions that have not yet completed the readjustment will form new leading bodies .
the report said : according to the CPC central committee 's appointment criteria , members of provincial - level party and government leading bodies should generally have a university degree or higher and a bachelor 's degree or higher .
the central authorities also stipulated that the new provincial party committee secretaries should be under the age of 59 and provincial governors under the age of 56 .
in addition , in order to strengthen the leadership of the CPC over people 's congresses at all levels , the chairmen of people 's congresses at all levels will all be concurrently party committee secretaries at the same level after the reshuffle of local governments is completed .
the source pointed out : beginning in march last year , 62 party and government leaders in 31 provinces , autonomous regions , and municipalities across the country have exchanged views and changed shifts .
so far last year , 14 provinces have completed the readjustment of their local party committees , including the secretaries of the six provinces , autonomous regions , and autonomous regions of inner mongolia , Jiangxi , Hubei , Hainan , Yunnan , and Qinghai .
in the governments of various provinces , municipalities directly under the central government , and autonomous regions , including the governors and mayors of Shanghai , Jiangxi , Shandong , Hunan , and Yunnan , a total of 11 provincial - and ministerial - level officials were transferred .
