new york , london rise in tandem
( comprehensive report ) us consumer confidence and industrial production both rose , rekindled confidence in the wall street market , and the three major indexes rose simultaneously , while the Dow Jones industrial and commercial index rose more steadily into the fifth week .
investors believe that as the us economy recovers and corporate profits are expected to rebound , Walmart , the chain with the highest turnover in the united states , and american express , the credit card issuer , will take the lead in soaring prices , bringing the Dow index to its longest weekly increase since september 2000 .
the Dow Jones industrial and commercial average closed friday at 10,607.23 , up 90.09 or 0.9% .
the us auto - quotation index reported 1868.30 points , up 14.16 points or 0.8% , while the broader s & p 500 index reported 1166.16 points , up 13.12 points or 1.1% .
for the whole week , the Dow rose slightly by 0.3% , expanding this year 's increase to 5.8% .
the s & p 500 edged up 0.2% , while the us auto index fell 3.2% to its first week of decline in three weeks .
the us consumer confidence index , released by the university of Michigan on friday , rose for the fifth time in six months to its highest level in 15 months , indicating that the economic recovery is not weak .
on the other hand , the industrial production index officially released by the united states rose 0.4% in february this year , which was better than originally expected by the market and the second rise in the past 17 months .
economists believe that these two figures have made the outline of the economic recovery clearer .
therefore , in the future , the trend of the market may also move toward more optimistic areas .
in the new york stock exchange , the rise - to - fall ratio was 4 to 3 , with 1.4 billion shares traded .
on the other hand , the ratio of stocks going up or down in the US auto @-@ quoted stock market is 6 to 5 .
on the british market , the possible layoffs from the record company EMI and the possibility that biotech company Celltech may stop selling shares have brought optimism to the market and pushed the stock market up 0.6% .
however , pharmaceutical manufacturer GlaxoSmithKline 's second - best - selling drug may face competition from its indian rivals , and the deutsche bank lowered its price forecast for Vodafone , the largest mobile phone operator in europe , limiting the index 's rise .
the london financial times index closed friday at 5,292.70 , up 31.30 points .
North Korean patrol boat accused of intruding into south Korean territorial waters
( Seoul , united states ) a south Korean official said that a north Korean patrol boat intruded into south Korean territorial waters yesterday .
the south Korean joint chiefs of staff said that the patrol boat crossed the yellow sea border 1.5 kilometers and stayed for 42 minutes before being chased away by south Korean warships .
it said that the north Korean patrol boat accidentally intruded into south Korean territorial waters while inspecting a Cambodian cargo ship .
the sea border between south korea and north korea is not obvious , and yesterday 's violation was the second time this year .
the ROK accused the DPRK of invading the western waters 12 times last year , but each time it was not serious .
in 1999 , a series of incursions by north Korean ships triggered the first maritime clash since the Korean war , sank a north Korean warship , and it is believed that 30 north Korean sailors lost their lives .
on the other hand , intelligence sources said that 25 north Korean defectors stayed at an army base in the philippines yesterday before flying to south korea for asylum .
