US official : Al Qaeda strengthens capital flow
( Washington , dc ) according to us media reports , a us official who declined to be named said the other day that al - Qaeda , the number one terrorist in the world , has increased its financial activities in recent weeks , indicating that some al - Qaeda leaders are regaining control over the organization and may seek to fund more attacks against us targets .
the official said that while al - Qaeda 's capital flow has increased , communication links between the surviving al - Qaeda members have also increased .
information intercepted by us intelligence agencies indicates that small groups of al - Qaeda members and Taliban militants are in contact .
most communications activities are concentrated in the north-western part of Pakistan , close to the Afghan border .
the official said that these activities show that some well - known al - Qaeda leaders are restoring control over the remnants of the terrorist organization , but the us official declined to name these people .
canistelaro , former director of the counter - terrorism department of the us central intelligence agency , said that there are numerous indications that al - Qaeda is being reorganized , and a large number of communications links between them are conducted through the internet , and money exchanges are very frequent .
canistelaro also said that there is some evidence that al - Qaeda 's leadership has also begun to become active .
