( comprehensive report from beijing ) Chen jinde , legislator of the democratic progressive party of Taiwan [ DPP ] , arrived in beijing yesterday for a visit with a delegation from several fishing organizations in Taiwan .
Chen jinde is the first DPP member to visit the mainland after chinese vice premier Qian Qichen issued a speech welcoming the broad masses of DPP members to visit the mainland in an appropriate capacity to commemorate the seventh anniversary of the founding of the Kuang Jiang at 8 : 00 p.m .
Chen jinde went to Hong kong on Saturday to obtain a visa and arrived in beijing yesterday for a 10 - day visit .
