after the chinese mainland banned the import of fishers to Taiwan , the fishery manpower in yilan region was seriously insufficient . in order to assist the fishing industry in the constituency , Chen jinde decided to join a delegation formed by the fishing association of beijing and Taiwan province to assist the fishing industry , hoping that the mainland would resume opening up the import of fishers to Taiwan .
the delegation , headed by Huang yongju , director general of the 13 regional fishing associations of Taiwan province , set off for beijing last Thursday in the name of the workers ' federation of the republic of china in Tseng .
another serious sandstorm in beijing
( Agence france - presse , beijing ) - china 's state media said another serious sandstorm occurred in beijing yesterday .
although the government has invested heavily in improving beijing 's environment and preventing the desert from approaching beijing , eliminating the sandstorms that occur frequently every year is still the main difficulty facing beijing , which plans to hold the 2008 olympic games .
China 's national meteorological bureau forecast that the first sandstorm this year hit beijing last friday , and the peak of cold air from mongolia is expected to cover beijing with grayish - yellow dust .
Yang weixi , chief engineer of the desert control center of the chinese ministry of forestry , told the beijing weekly newspaper : " I dare not say that there will be no sandstorms in 2008 .
what we can do is to control the man - made factors that produce dust storms and prevent desertification of the environment .
he said , however , natural factors beyond people 's control , such as wind , drought , and great deserts , make it impossible for china to avoid sandstorms in the short term .
the chinese government has pledged to invest 56.8 billion yuan ( 12.376 billion Singapore dollars ) between 2002 and 2008 to prevent desertification and reduce the occurrence of dust storms .
Beijing alone will spend about 1 billion yuan ( 220 million Singapore dollars ) this year .
an expert from the chinese academy of forestry sciences said : the increase in the yuan 's financial appropriations will greatly improve the situation . however , it may take several decades before we can see the results of the rectification work .
after conducting an investigation at the beginning of this year , chinese environmental experts warned : about one - third of china 's territory is now desert . this is mainly caused by human economic activities , such as overgrazing .
the report said that in the first six months of last year , 18 sandstorms occurred in beijing , all of which originated in inner mongolia , and 60% of inner mongolia 's land was desert .
at the national people 's congress session , which just concluded this month , deputies from Shanghai , beijing , and inner mongolia urged the government to build a green great wall ( made up of trees ) to stop sandstorms .
according to a report by the Shanghai star , Xu shiyuan , vice president of the chinese geographic society , warned that if the government does not take emergency measures , sandstorms may even hit Shanghai .
fake diplomas are rampant in china , and many serving cadres have been found to be holding false certificates
( comprehensive report from Hong kong ) fake diplomas are rampant in mainland china . the Guangdong provincial employment guidance center for college graduates recently appraised the credentials of 15 officials sent by a city in the chaoshan region . seven of them were confirmed to be fake by the naked eye .
according to a Hong kong newspaper report , since the center began its certification work in may last year , it has so far accepted more than 3,500 diplomas , accounting for more than 800 fake diplomas of various kinds , and the fake certificate ratio is as high as 23% .
according to the report , the majority of these fake certificates are adult education and self - study examination certificates , of which two thirds are forged on the streets and one third are issued in violation of regulations by regular educational institutions .
the responsible person of the center also disclosed that since the appraisal department was set up at the same time as it was undergoing organizational reform , the departments and enterprises and institutions that were sent for inspection generally had a very high proportion of false certificates , and many of the owners of false certificates were cadres on the job .
with the approval of relevant departments of the ministry of education , the Guangdong provincial employment guidance center for college graduates is currently the only institution in china authorized to carry out nationwide certification of higher education qualifications .
the responsible person also disclosed that out of consideration for selecting officials , the state - owned bank of a prefecture - level city sent 36 middle - level officials and backbone business personnel their diplomas for appraisal , and only six of the results were true .
it has been learned that along with the appraisal process , many private enterprises have also come to request the appraisal . the main items they appraise are job applicants and newly recruited university students .
the appraisal department found that many of the college students ' certificates were also fake .
last year , a large enterprise set up a branch office somewhere in the pearl river delta and recruited a number of university students .
the boss sent more than 30 employee certificates for appraisal and found that 10 of them were fake .
in recent years , quite a number of other provincial institutions have set up branches in Guangdong province that are not qualified to issue academic certificates . however , in order to attract students , they have falsified their enrollment , claiming to be able to issue state - recognized certificates and issuing a number of fake certificates to students upon graduation .
25 North Koreans seeking asylum arrive in Seoul
( Seoul road transmission ) 25 north Koreans seeking asylum arrived at Seoul international airport yesterday to start a new life in south korea .
after they passed , they waved and smiled at the Korean television camera .
Li song , a 43 - year - old factory worker , told an impromptu press conference at the airport : " we hope to settle here and live in a world of freedom and hope . "
another man said : " since south korea is a free country , i did not hesitate to risk my life to come here . "
this group of north Koreans broke into the spanish embassy in beijing last Thursday , firmly indicating that they wanted to go to the ROK .
China allowed them to go to Seoul via the Philippines on Friday .
they come from six families , two of which have no parents .
they are the largest group of fugitives since the end of the Korean war .
according to the Seoul national intelligence agency , this group of people will join the 2,000 north Koreans who have already settled in south korea , 138 of whom only joined the south korea this year .
last year , 583 people went to south korea to break the record .
the 25 new arrivals will attend an orientation class at a government shelter near the capital Seoul .
the primary objective of the course is to help defectors overcome the tension of flight and then receive counselling to adapt to Korean culture , including an understanding of capitalism .
the final step is to be trained for a new job .
new Yorker weekly : Iraqi intelligence agencies have been in close contact with al - Qaeda for many years
( Washington , dc ) the latest issue of the weekly " new Yorker " reports that iraq 's intelligence agencies have for many years maintained close ties with al - Qaeda led by Osama , the mastermind of the september 11 incident .
it is learned that the two organizations jointly command a terrorist organization in northern iraq 's Kurdistan region .
the us central intelligence agency has always been sceptical of the allegation that Iraqi president Hussein and al - Qaeda are linked .
in the past , hawkish officials in the bush administration who support military action against iraq have been trying to find evidence of links between Hussein and al - Qaeda .
these officials greatly praised this report of the weekly " new Yorker " the day before yesterday , and pointed out that the relevant report is the latest basis for supporting their arguments .
according to the report , there is an Ansar islamic guerrilla force composed of Kurds and Arabs in iraq 's Kurdistan region . all members of the guerrilla force have received training in the Osama camp .
Goldberg , the author of the report , said he interviewed several agents of Ansar islamic guerrillas captured by the pro - us Kurdish patriotic union , who claimed that Ansar islamic guerrillas were jointly commanded by Hussein and al - Qaeda , and that some al - Qaeda fighters in afghanistan had fled to the Iraqi Kurdish region controlled by Ansar islamic guerrillas .
the agents also said that iraq hosted a al - Qaeda leader of Egyptian origin in Baghdad in 1992 .
US officials warned that the Kurdish patriotic union might make a big fuss about the reports in order to justify the us plan to overthrow the Hussein regime .
