street crime on the rise : Britain sends more police on patrol
( London , united states news agency ) the british government is committed to solving the increasingly serious street crime problem and will send more police patrols .
Interior minister Blunkett said that to curb the rising cases of street robberies and violence , it is necessary to send more police to step up patrols .
he said : " we really should straighten out the order in the streets because law - abiding citizens want to be able to walk safely on the streets and live in peace without fear of being attacked . "
although the overall crime rate in britain has declined , the number of street crimes has increased by 13% between 2000 and 2001 .
the situation in london was even more alarming , with 19,248 robberies reported in september and november 2001 alone , more than double the 8,614 reported in the same period of the previous year .
the government also said that the increase in crime was mainly due to a large increase in cell phone robberies , with more than 700,000 cell phone robberies occurring nationwide last year .
this is the first time that the british police have focused on cracking down on street hooligans and robberies . in the past , they have focused on cracking down on illegal possession of guns and selling narcotics on the streets .
the new plan will first be implemented in 10 neighborhoods where street crime cases are concentrated .
the police will step up patrols in these neighbourhoods and provide more protection to the victims .
