( Agence france - presse , beijing ) - workers from 10 state - owned factories in Liaoning city , northeast china 's Liaoning province , staged a mass demonstration yesterday to protest wage arrears and pensions , low retrenchment fees , and corruption .
meanwhile , demonstrations by dismissed oil workers in Daqing city in Heilongjiang province have been going on for three weeks .
the china human rights and democracy movement information center in Hong kong said that the Liaoyang city public security bureau arrested a 54 - year - old Yao fuxin , the organizer of the demonstration , on Sunday . at the same time , it is also pursuing more than 10 other workers who organized the demonstration .
according to Yao 's relative , who declined to be named , he went shopping and did not come back . several people saw him being taken away .
in addition , at the Daqing oil field in the neighboring province of Heilongjiang , the police and the Daqing petroleum administration told reporters that the sit-in demonstration by dismissed oil workers has entered its third week , but the number of workers participating in the sit-in has decreased from 50,000 at the beginning to more than 1,000 .
