the investigation report of the SIA air crash has repeatedly been delayed by the Taiwan Aviation Safety Commission , and prosecutors have questioned the existence of a mystery .
( Taipei ) it has been one and a half years since the sinking of the SIA plane crash , but the investigation report of the Taiwan aviation safety committee has been delayed again and again , causing the Taoyuan district procurator 's office to stall its investigation , prosecutors have questioned the existence of a mystery , and the aviation safety council has promised to deliver the investigation report in april .
at 11:18 on the evening of 31 october 2000 , Singapore airlines flight SQ - 006 from zhongzheng airport to los Angeles of the united states mistakenly ran into the right runway of runway 05 and collided with two dredgers on the runway , causing explosions , killing 83 passengers and injuring nearly 100 others .
China times reported yesterday that the Taoyuan district procurator 's office , which was responsible for investigating criminal responsibility after the plane crash , had many disputes with the aviation security unit that investigated the flight safety accident because of its power of investigation .
since the plane crash occurred , wang Tim - Sheng , chief procurator of the Taoyuan district procuratorate , has been promoted to chief procurator of Taichung . Chen shouhuang has taken over the post . Huang Mou - shin , procurator - in - charge , has also been transferred to the northern procuratorate . Jiang yuan - Zhen has taken over the case .
however , the aviation security council originally indicated that it would complete the investigation report by the end of last year , which was postponed to the end of january , and then changed its plan to complete it in february after january . so far , no results have been achieved . on the urging of the procurators , the aviation security council promised to deliver the report in april .
as the destination of flight SQ - 006 is los Angeles , some of the families of the victims have filed huge civil claims in us courts , not only against Singapore airlines , but also against Taiwan 's civil aviation authority .
the claim of the family members of the victims is tantamount to accusing the Taiwan pagoda air traffic controllers of negligence . therefore , the investigation conclusions of the Taoyuan district attorney 's office are particularly conspicuous .
