global warming warns of complete collapse of antarctic ice shelf
( comprehensive report from auckland ) experts from the us national ice and snow data center said yesterday that an ice shelf in the antarctic has completely collapsed and split into thousands of icebergs , the largest such incident in 30 years , thus again warning against global warming .
according to reports , an ice shelf on the Larsen continental margin , covering an area of 3,250 square kilometers near the east coast of Antarctica , has completely collapsed in 35 days .
the center warns that other ice shelves are on the verge of collapse as the hot summer approaches .
this indicates that the glacier flow in Antarctica will increase and the global sea level will rise , causing harm to lowland areas .
the center , which is located at the university of colorado , said on its website ( nsidc.org ) that the Larsen continental edge ice shelf b , which weighs 720 billion tons of ice , may have broken up since january 31 this year , and broken ice has formed thousands of floating icebergs in the Weddell sea .
the center also said that the breakup of the ice shelf is due to the warming of the region .
