( comprehensive report from london ) the results of an opinion poll released yesterday show that more than half of british voters disapprove of the government 's support for the us attack on iraq .
a poll conducted by the Guardian and pollster ICM showed that 51 percent of voters oppose the British support for the US attack on Iraq .
this is contrary to similar polls last year and three years ago , when the majority of british voters supported the attack on iraq .
a similar poll released the day before yesterday by the us cable news network and the " times " weekly showed that 70% of Americans support the government 's attack on iraq to overthrow the Hussein regime .
