so far this year , three yellow dust weather events have occurred in Seoul , south korea .
the south Korean meteorological agency forecast yesterday that a large amount of dust raised by strong updrafts in deserts such as china and mongolia would spread over northern china and pass through south korea by northwest wind .
enough to destroy a medium - sized planet and rub shoulders with the earth
( AFP , melbourne , Florida ) a small planet large enough to destroy a medium - sized city passed the earth at a close distance of 463,000 kilometers without being discovered earlier . astronomers learned about this only four days later .
the small planet , about 50 meters in diameter , comes from the direction of the sun , making it difficult for astronomers to find it .
the small planet passed the earth on march 8 , but by the time it was discovered on march 12 , the small planet had already gone far away .
Williams , based at the International Astronomical Society &apos;s Small Planet Center in Cambridge , Massachusetts , helped locate the small planet .
astronomically speaking , this small planet is very close to the earth because the moon is 400,000 kilometers away from the earth .
Williams told the Florida Today News on Wednesday : the key is that the stars should have been detected before coming from the direction of the sun .
only in this way can astronomers determine as soon as possible the orbit of the small planet and predict whether it will hit the earth .
in 1908 , when a large or small star collided with the earth , it collided with a pit 32 kilometers wide in the forests of Siberia .
