illegal access to china 's state secrets and bribery of chinese - american engineers sentenced to five years in prison
( Beijing , united states ) beijing 's no . 1 intermediate people 's court yesterday sentenced Fang fuming , an american chinese engineer , to five years ' imprisonment on charges of illegally obtaining state secrets and offering bribes on behalf of a company .
the case has aroused protests in the united states .
a spokesman for the us embassy in china said that Fang Fuming will be deported after serving his prison term .
the sentence will be adjusted according to the length of time he has already been imprisoned .
the us embassy sent a diplomat to the hearing .
Fang fuming 's representative lawyer said that his client had already been in prison for two years , but china said it had not been that long .
Xinhua news agency confirmed the verdict .
it said that from 1995 to 1999 , Fang fuming obtained 35 documents containing state secrets and bribed chinese civil servants with 245,000 us dollars ( currently about 450,000 Singapore dollars ) to assist foreign investors in bidding for china 's power projects .
Fang Fuming is an electrical engineering consultant for foreign companies in China and elsewhere in Asia .
Fang fuming 's representative lawyer Cohen said that Fang fuming denied paying bribes , saying that he was a victim of corrupt chinese power officials .
Fang fuming used to be a chinese power official and became a us citizen in 1994 .
in the past two years , a group of us citizens and residents were among those charged with violating china 's national security law .
the detention of Fang Fuming once strained sino - us relations .
the us government has repeatedly protested china 's handling of Fang Fuming 's case , pointing out that the authorities ' detention of Fang Fuming for several months without trial violates international norms .
Fang fuming 's family said that he was badly treated .
his wife and two children are us citizens .
Cohen said that Fang fuming was detained on 28 february 2000 , but the detention period proposed by the chinese foreign ministry was 28 august 2000 .
China cancels naval task force 's visit to the united states and is unwilling to confirm whether hu Jintao will visit the united states as originally planned .
( comprehensive report from beijing ) sino - us relations , which had once warmed up as a result of us president bush 's visit to china , are rapidly cooling down . China confirmed yesterday that it would cancel plans for a naval fleet to visit us ports this year and refused to confirm whether vice president hu Jintao would visit the united states as originally planned .
answering a regular reporter 's question , foreign ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said : as far as i know , the chinese naval task force is preparing to visit as planned , and their plan does not include us ports .
when a reporter asked her twice whether hu Jintao 's plan to visit the united states had been affected , and asked whether an earlier reply could be interpreted as meaning that hu Jintao 's visit to the united states in april would continue as scheduled , Zhang Qiyue declined to comment or confirm .
Zhang Qiyue only repeatedly accused the united states of making a series of violations of the three sino - us joint communiques in a short period of one month after bush 's visit to china , and demanded that the united states stop using the Taiwan issue to interfere in china 's internal affairs .
on the other hand , in washington , the united states ignored china 's warning that sino - us relations were blowing in a cold wind on Wednesday , insisting that it was not inappropriate for the united states to allow Taiwan 's defense minister to attend the us - Taiwan defense summit in Florida .
Beijing repeatedly criticized the united states for issuing visas to Taiwan defense minister tang Yao - ming to attend a meeting sponsored by us arms dealers earlier this month .
Tang Yao - ming also met with two senior us officials at that time .
State council spokesman Boucher was questioned by reporters at a regular news conference about china 's complaint about the incident , but he clearly tried his best to avoid a verbal war with china .
he said : after this round of talks , our stand is known to all .
you have to ask me this question every day , i 'm willing to explain it every day , china has to ask this question every day , we 're willing to explain it every day .
he said : Zhang 's stand has not changed . these are normal contacts between us and the Taiwanese people , and we will continue to do so .
Zhang Qiyue also confirmed a russian media report yesterday , saying that chinese state president Jiang Zemin had a telephone conversation with russian president Putin at his request the night before yesterday . the two sides mainly exchanged views on the issue of mutually beneficial cooperation between china and russia .
both sides held that mutually beneficial cooperation between china and russia conforms to the interests of the two countries and the two peoples .
